[[File:M<U+00E9>daille Africaine bar.jpg|150px|thumb|3 of the 4 possible clasps to the 1940-1945 African War Medal]]
The '''1940-1945 African War Medal''' ({{lang-fr|M<U+00E9>daille de la Guerre Africaine 1940-1945}}, {{lang-nl|Afrikaanse Oorlogsmedaille 1940-1945}}) was a [[Belgium|Belgian]] war service [[medal]] established by [[royal decree]] of the [[Prince Charles, Count of Flanders|Regent]] on 30 January 1947 and awarded to officers and soldiers for at least one year's service in the [[Force Publique]] between 10 May 1940 and 7 May 1945.  This service was not limited to the Belgian colonies of the [[Belgian Congo|Congo]] and [[Ruanda-Urundi]] but also included the [[Middle East]], [[Nigeria]], [[Madagascar]] and [[Burma]], for which clasps were awarded for six months service in those areas<ref name="decree">{{cite web  | authorlink = Belgian government | title = Royal Decree of the Regent of 30 January 1947 creating the 1940-1945 African War Medal | publisher = Belgian Government| date = 1947-01-30 }}</ref>. 
   
==Award description==
The 1940-1945 African War Medal was a 52mm high (including suspension) by 33mm wide rectangular medal struck from bronze with sloped upper shoulders and rounded lower corners.  Its [[obverse]] bore the relief images of the left profiles of a native African soldier wearing a [[fez]] and of a helmeted Belgian soldier, both within a recessed central area.  Under the recess, the embossed years "1940 - 1945".  The reverse was plain<ref name="decree"/>. 

Four clasps were issued for wear on the ribbon inscribed in French<ref name="decree"/>:
*NIGERIE for six months service in Nigeria
*MOYEN-ORIENT for six months service in the Middle East
*MADAGASCAR for six months service in Madagascar
*BIRMANIE for six months service in Burma

[[Belgian Air Component|Air force]] personnel who served in theatre whether on an operational combat or transport unit received the medal with a miniature set of bronze wings on the ribbon<ref name="decree"/>. 

The 1940-1945 African War Medal was suspended by a ring passing laterally though a suspension loop at the top of the medal, from a 37mm wide light blue silk [[moir<U+00E9>]] ribbon with a 5mm wide central yellow stripe and 3mm wide yellow stripes situated 5mm from the ribbon edges<ref name="decree"/>. 

